emotes.msg: Hea Arantah looks around his town brazenly.
Hea Arantah belches softly.
Hea Arantah's arm moves suddenly, too quickly to see, and snatches a small flying insect out of the air. He hums a merry child's tune, and methodically pulls its wings and legs off.
The youthful voice of Hea Arantah mutters, "When, my friends? Soon? ...Very well, I understand." He seems to be talking to the fountain, though his eyes are glazed and glowing faintly.
Hea Arantah's youthful voice shouts, "We have freedom, my friends! The islands are open to us!" The residents of the town hoot a loud Tumerok cheer.
Hea Arantah wipes spilled liquor from his lips. His voice cracks as he cries, "Aren't we mighty? Don't the Aun cower in their beds in fear of us?" The residents cheer again... somewhat uncertainly.
All at once, the youthful voice of Hea Arantah screams across the square. While the visiting Isparians look at him in confusion, the Hea bury themselves in their work.
Arantah gasps, clutching at his head. His eyes are shut tight, but a painful violet light burns out from behind his eyelids.
"WHAT? What did I do? Yes... I understand. The upland patrols. Reinforced. At once, Collector. Please... my xuta is watching."
The light ceases like a snuffed candle. The Tah of Hea staggers.
"Warriors!" he calls, rather weakly. "I want raiding parties on the plateau at once! Temenua isn't doing his task... our friends are angry!"
ChampionKillQuest1@GiveFigurine
ArantahBoon1
ArantahBoon2
ArantahBoon3
ArantahBoon4
ArantahBoon5
Young Arantah's eyes narrow as he reads furiously.
...What? What is this? No! They said... they said I was the only one! This can't be true! What does this mean?
Arantah crushes the journal in his fist, then methodically begins to tear it to pieces.
They lied to me.
His eyes glower a dark, thunderhead purple.
They lied to me.
As the pieces of Martine's journal flutter towards the ground, they burst into flames.
I'm more powerful than this stupid man-thing. The first. The best. I'll show them. Them and their man-puppet.
ChampionKillQuest1@Use
Hea Arantah tells you, "You're %s! They told me what you did - you killed that poacher Ralirea! Give me his figurine. Quickly, quickly!"
Ah! I can tell by the flickering of your keh that you have broken one of the Aun's precious rocks in the last few weeks.
My atual arutoa brothers like to see the wharu running free across this land.
So, this is the face of one of the stonebreakers the Aun hate, eh? A drink to the enemy of my enemy.
My atual arutoa brothers like to see the wharu running free. They collect them, you know.
Young Arantah belches softly, and you catch the fetid odor of a poor imitation of distilled Empyrean dew.
ArantahKill1@GiveFigurine
Wow, great! Ha ha! I warned them not to send their hunters on to my plateau!

Young Arantah clutches his fist around the little figurine, so tightly the veins in his wrist stand in relief. His eyes flash violet, and after a muffled crunch, clay dust begins to trickle through his fingers. He looks up at you and grins boyishly.
That was a trick my friends taught me, way back when I was driven from Timaru. I could do the same to your head, you know.
I'm kidding! You've been a friend the Hea, and I reward my friends. Here...
Arantah places his hand on your forehead and his eyes glow blue-white. You feel... enlightened...
You have gained a skill point!
Ha! Yes, this was given to you by Aun Kahmaula, right? He threw stones at me. I was only ten... I needed that bread to live, damn it!
Arantah's eyes flare with inchoate rage, casting violet light upon the ground. Around you, the residents cringe and hold their breath... But a smile breaks across his face.
Well, I'm glad to see him set back, anyway. Here. A gift from my atual arutoa allies.
From the medicine pouch of Aun Gehaua, I see? Great! I got this from my atual arutoa friends. My warriors and I often raided this area in the early years of our alliance.
I wonder whatever happened to that damned portal mage of theirs? He cost me a nice wrap. Did you know human children make the softest leather?
Ah, this still resonates with the keh of Aun Tanaua, the old fool who talks to rocks.
Anyway, here's a little something the atual arutoa gave me. I hear they use this a lot themselves, as a stop on their way to talk to those turtle-nosed freaks in the south.
Aun Laiaua's mark is on this. He always seemed like a dull old worry-wart to me. Going on and on about the how the atual arutoa were soulless and all. Stupid.
The Aun never thought that the atual arutoa have no anima because they ARE the anima of the universe. At least, that's how I understood what they told me.
Young Arantah's eyes glitter with mad glee at the sight of the figurine.
Aun Aanaua has cursed you! Wonderful! This means Wharu runs free, and Aun are pressed! Now is the time for me to release my raiders!
Now THIS gift of the atual arutoa - you'll LIKE this one! Now go.
RingQuest01@Use
Young Arantah glowers at you.

What do you want, man-thing? Be quick, and do not lie, for the atual arutoa have given me many eyes to see the truth with. Annoy me at your own risk, for my anger is quick and my power great... As the Aun have learned.
Young Arantah looks annoyed - which seems to be his natural state.
What? Can't you see I'm busy? I have many responsibilities here!
That Aun hunter, for one. What's his name?
Arantah belches loudly as Nyrinua calls over, "Ralirea, my Tah."
Ralirea, yes. Don't CORRECT me, Nyri.
Anyway, this old Aun dustongue - Ralirea - poaches the gromnies of my plateau! If someone would kill him, and bring me that figurine he wears within a day as proof...
A suspicious scowl lumbers across the young Tumerok chieftain's face.
Hea Arantah tells you, "Now wait. My memory isn't what it used to be since the atual arutoa... bettered me, but I do remember your face, %s."

Hea Arantah tells you, "Yes... I rewarded you for Ralirea's death before. That means this figurine must be a fake! You dare try to fool the mighty friend of the atual? Go away before I use my Grip on you!"

Ha! Your keh is all wrong! You were not the one who slew Ralirea this day - someone else did, and gave you his totem. Tell your friend to come and collect my reward himself, I am too important to deal with errand-runners.
What? Are you KIDDING? I already rewarded you for breaking the stones of the north in the last three months. Flee from me now, beggar, or I'll use my Grip on you!
Arantah throws the clay totem at you!
What? Are you KIDDING? I already rewarded you for breaking the stones of the northeast in the last three months. Flee from me now, beggar, or I'll use my Grip on you!
Arantah throws the clay totem at you!
What? Are you KIDDING? I already rewarded you for breaking the stones of the southeast in the last three months. Flee from me now, beggar, or I'll use my Grip on you!
Arantah throws the clay totem at you!
What? Are you KIDDING? I already rewarded you for breaking the stones of the southwest in the last three months. Flee from me now, beggar, or I'll use my Grip on you!
Arantah throws the clay totem at you!
What? Are you KIDDING? I already rewarded you for breaking the stones of the northwest in the last three months. Flee from me now, beggar, or I'll use my Grip on you!
Arantah throws the clay totem at you!
